Step 1: Compute Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Total Owner's Equity = 16,112,375.10  
• Total Liabilities = Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity – Total Owner's Equity  
  = 23,717,525.01 – 16,112,375.10  
  = 7,605,149.91  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = 7,605,149.91 / 16,112,375.10 ≈ 0.47  

Step 2: Compute Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 112,375.10 and Total Revenue = 775,598.77  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (112,375.10 / 775,598.77) × 100  
  ≈ 14.49%  

Step 3: Compute Return on Assets (ROA)  
• Total Assets (end) = 23,717,525.01  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100  
  = (112,375.10 / 23,717,525.01) × 100  
  ≈ 0.47%  

Step 4: Compute Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• Accounts Receivable (start) = 0.00, and (end) = 321,015.98  
• Average Accounts Receivable = (0.00 + 321,015.98) / 2  
  = 160,507.99  
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
  = 775,598.77 / 160,507.99  
  ≈ 4.83  

Thus, the solution is:  

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.47",
    "Net Profit Margin": "14.49%",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "0.47%",
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "4.83"
  }
}
